DATA CLOUD
Update Data Cloud to Enhanced Security Data Spaces

All Data Cloud orgs start receiving new standard permission sets on a rolling basis in November 2023. Users who aren’t assigned to new permission sets before your org enables enhanced security data spaces lose access to data-space aware Data Cloud features.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To assign permission sets:	

Assign Permission Sets

AND

View Setup and Configuration

Complete these steps to migrate your org to enhanced data space security.

NOTE You don’t need to clone the standard permission sets if they’re suitable out-of-the-box for users in your org. Clone standard permission sets only if you need to create variations, such as to grant different levels of access to users in different departments. For example, if you have different marketing managers for different data spaces, clone the standard permission sets to create one custom permission set for each group of marketing managers.
To create several variations on the new standard permission sets, clone them.
Associate the new permission sets with Data Spaces. You can associate more than one data space with a single permission set.
Assign permission sets to Data Cloud users or migrate permission sets using user access policies.
After users have been granted new permission sets, in Data Cloud Setup, click Data Spaces.
To turn on enhanced security data spaces, click Enable.
Remove legacy permission sets from Data Cloud users manually or using user access policies.
Migrate Data Cloud Permission Sets using User Access Policies
Learn how to use user access policies to grant updated Data Cloud permission sets to groups of users based on criteria you set.
